(1638, 764, 'content_3_description', '<h3>Front-end Development is a joke</h3>\r\nPer the <a class=\"bx ff gf gg gh gi\" href=\"https://timber.github.io/docs/guides/acf-cookbook/#flexible-content-field\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Timber Docs</a> I open up a loop and am looping through the ‘content’ field. This is the name of my Flexible Layout field I just created with ACF. I am taking advantage of the Twig templating engine and have each of my components in their own respective files and use Twig’s <code class=\"ha il im in io b\">{% include %}</code> functionality to include each component. Just look at how clean this looks compared to a typical WP theme 😍.'),
